          "description": "I was a new patient. I went in for a 6 month cleaning. As a new patient, x-rays were taken of my teeth, as I would expect. The dentist then looked at my teeth. My teeth were not cleaned by a hygienist. The dentist did the procedure. He clearly had somewhere else to go because he only spent five minutes cleaning my teeth before sending me on my way. FIVE MINUTES.\n\nAdd to this, there was music blaring in the waiting room and the examination room. It was the most unprofessional medical experience I\u2019ve ever had.\n\nThe only redeeming aspect of the visit was the woman at the front desk. She was quite pleasant. She also seemed surprised I was done so quickly.",
